================================================================================
PATCH: HTML/EN/settings/server/status.html
================================================================================
Description:
  Extends the server status web template to display the internet
  access section between server status and Perl module versions.

Changes:
  - Adds PROCESS infoItem for INFORMATION_MENU_INTERNET_ACCESS
  - Position: after SERVER_STATUS, before INFORMATION_MENU_PERL
  - Uses internetaccess.items (provided by Status.pm)
  - Renders section title and status lines

Template Processing:
  The infoItem block renders:
    - Section header with translated title
    - Individual items (HTTP status, HTTPS status)
    - Proxy information if configured
    - All text properly localized via string tokens

Technical Details:
  - Template Toolkit syntax: [% PROCESS infoItem ... %]
  - Variable names match provider registration names
  - Section ordering controlled by template line order
  - Renders for all supported languages (17 languages)

Requirements:
  - Status.pm must provide internetaccess variable
  - strings.txt must contain all INTERNET_ACCESS_* strings
  - Browser must support UTF-8 encoding

Author: Markus Baier
Date: 2025-12-28
================================================================================

--- a/HTML/EN/settings/server/status.html	2025-12-28 01:27:49.271043836 +0100
+++ b/HTML/EN/settings/server/status.html	2025-12-28 03:23:07.354837673 +0100
@@ -52,6 +52,7 @@
 [% END %]
 
 [% PROCESS infoItem title="SERVER_STATUS" items=server.items %]
+[% PROCESS infoItem title="INFORMATION_MENU_INTERNET_ACCESS" items=internetaccess.items %]
 [% PROCESS infoItem title="INFORMATION_MENU_PERL" items=perl.items %]
 
 [% IF library; PROCESS infoItem title="INFORMATION_MENU_LIBRARY" items=library.items; END %]
